2:19 AM
the thing i'd say would help the most is looking into some more vocal mixing techniques. i think the overall sound could benefit from some eq- ing to make it less boomy and sit better with the other elements. other suggestion would be see if you can come up with like a counter melody to the vocal, the piano and later the synth are playing the exact same melody as the vocal. it could be nice to have a little more going on like a harmony. But besides that, you can hear you're trying some cool things with different effects and stuff in different sections to make them sound different from eachother, keep it up

ok so for libraries, there's this stuff for kontakt and decent sampler called pianobook. its a thing where ppl can submit their own sampled instruments (so despite the name its not only piano, theres some guitars and stuff on there as well), in the same style i believe labs (from spitfire audio) has some guitar stuff as well. then theres the more well known stuff like realguitar and ample
11:32 PM
for effects and amp sims and such, guitar rig is just other than that there's often lots of distortion and common effects built into most daws and combined with some convolution to do cab sims and stuff you can get some cool sounds as well, basically building your own amp

Midnight Tide 2022-10-26 12:34 AM
Also, I know you work a lot with a producer, but do have tips on how to get a song to have a more full and professional sound
DecemberAir 2022-10-26 12:34 AM
EQ is big.
12:35 AM
Knowing when and where to cut and roll different frequencies so they fit better together so the whole song doesn’t sound like a muddy mess is important cus that’s your base
12:36 AM
I do some of it to an extent but it gets really complicated for like top of the line stuff
12:38 AM
Also layering. Layer your synths, pianos, strings, etc. Find sounds that fit well together and have them play the same notes, but an octave higher or lower. Or some variation of that.
12:38 AM
I’d also say make sure you have one stand out layer and the rest be more complimentary
12:38 AM
So don’t have them all at the same volume
12:40 AM
Panning sounds are big too. Make your mixes sound wider. If everything is coming from the same spot, and you don’t pan certain instruments left or right at all, it can muddy everything and sound one dimensional
